@rhatdan, the problem with running on a default EL7 is that the XFS mounts don't have the `ftype` flag enabled for overlayfs by default, so it takes some surgery to resolve it (shuffling files/remounting etc.).

The goal of this was to come up with a method that could be quickly applied to existing docker systems without outage.

I will re-create and remount the XFS in a test VM and confirm it works with the default location.
